                                        <due></due>
                            <votes>1</votes>
                                    <watches>2</watches>
                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="12899622" author="jdcryans" created="Tue, 17 Aug 2010 22:26:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch that adds a new utility method to HBaseTestingUtility to get the region server that holds the first region in a table, which is used to select the right server in TestLogRolling. Test now passes 100% of the time (on 8 runs).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12899633" author="lars_francke" created="Tue, 17 Aug 2010 22:49:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Applied the patch, ran the test five times. Everything looks fine now. Thanks for finding and fixing this!&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12899764" author="stack" created="Wed, 18 Aug 2010 07:32:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;+1 though I do not like your addition to HBaseTestingUtiliy.  My guess is that this test is only test that will use the added method.  We shoudl be a little judicious about what we add HTU.  We don&apos;t want it to be turn into a hard to maintain dumping ground.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="12900453" author="jdcryans" created="Thu, 19 Aug 2010 20:58:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I refactored TestScannerTimeout to use the new tool too, which is now more commented. Committed to trunk.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15017290" author="lars_francke" created="Fri, 20 Nov 2015 12:42:35 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This issue was closed as part of a bulk closing operation on 2015-11-20. All issues that have been resolved and where all fixVersions have been released have been closed (following discussions on the mailing list).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
